subSubSection.paragraph:
Male genitalia (
Fig. 58
). Uncus slender in basal part, distinctly expanded terminally; socius slender, drooping; arm of gnathos and terminal plate fairly large; valva subtriangular; sacculus long, slender, convex beyond 1/3 where terminally bifid process present, with slender pointed free termination; transtilla interrupted medially, armed with very large sublateral hooks; juxta small; aedeagus small, pointed ventroterminally; coecum penis very short; no cornuti in vesica.
